cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the complexity of mu-calculus model checking over graphs given by n-HPDA, which is a logical problem.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper deals with Higher Order Pushdown Automata and reachability games, which are topics related to automata theory.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of a problem and involves algorithmic techniques.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper deals with automata and games, which are topics related to programming languages.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of a problem and involves complexity theory.
